Retention
Pedi STAT Software may retain your personal information up to one year following a request for the deletion of your account, subject to applicable law. Thereafter, the data will be archived or anonymized.
Additional Terms for Residents of the European Economic Area ("EEA")
If you are a resident of the EEA, legislation permits you to request that we tell you what personal information we hold about you and how we process it and that we provide you with a copy of that information. You are also entitled to access, rectify, change, update, delete, revoke, or improve upon your personal information at any time. When the personal data processing is based on your consent, you have the right to withdraw your consent concerning such data processing, at any time, without affecting the lawfulness of processing based on consent before your withdrawal. You can exercise these rights free of charge. We may ask you to provide further information to confirm your identity before considering your request. To make such a request, please send an email to
James M Kempema MD PA
or write to us at 445 W 6th Ave #201, Vancouver, BC V5Y 1L3 Canada. Additionally, you have a right to complain to your local data protection authority if you are concerned about how your personal data is used through or in the context of the Services.
For purposes of providing the Services, Pedi STAT Software may transfer your personal information (including user-provided information) to servers located in the United States or Canada. By using and continuing to use the Services, you agree to that transfer.
The personal information we hold is used solely for the purposes of operating the Services and communicating with you. You are also entitled to object to any processing of your personal information on reasonable grounds. We make no automated decisions about you that create legal effects or otherwise significantly affect you.
As discussed above, we have implemented technology and security measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, disclosure, improper use, alteration, unlawful or accidental destruction, and accidental loss.
We use security methods to determine the identity of registered users, so that appropriate rights and restrictions can be enforced for these users. If you are a registered user, we use both logins and passwords to authenticate you. You are responsible for maintaining the security of your login credentials.
By using the Services or providing personal information to us, you agree that we may communicate with you electronically about security, privacy, and administrative issues relating to your use of the Services. If you have a reason to believe that your interaction with us is no longer secure, please contact us immediately at
James M Kempema MD PA
.
